SIMPLE: sea_otter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea otter
<hw>Sea" ot"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An aquatic
carnivore (<spn>Enhydris lutris</spn> syn. <spn>Enhydris marina</spn>)
found in the <geog>North Pacific Ocean</geog>. Its fur is highly valued,
especially by the Chinese. It is allied to the common otter, but is
larger, with feet more decidedly webbed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sea-otter's cabbage</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
gigantic kelp of the Pacific Ocean (<spn>Nereocystis Lutkeana</spn>).
See <er>Nereocystis</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea owl</ent>⟦br⟧
